tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  103,1,"Allah may He be glorified takes an oath on time."
  104,1,"Evil consequences and a severe punishment awaits the one who frequently backbites the people and taunts them."
  104,2,"The one whose only concern is to amass wealth and count it; he has no other concern."
  104,5,"O Messenger! What do you know of this fire that smashes everything that is thrown into it?"
  104,7,"The fire that penetrates the bodies of the people until it reaches their hearts."
  105,2,"Allah made their evil plot to destroy it in vain; they did not achieve what they desired in trying to turn the people away from the Kaâ€˜bah. They did not succeed in the slightest."
  105,4,"They pelted them with stones of clay."
  105,5,"So Allah made them like the leaves of crops that have been eaten and trampled upon by livestock."